</div>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:182px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Pythagorean.svg" class="image" title="The Pythagorean theorem: The sum of the areas of the two squares on the legs (a and b) equals the area of the square on the hypotenuse (c)."><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d2/Pythagorean.svg/180px-Pythagorean.svg.png" width="180" height="143" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Pythagorean.svg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
The Pythagorean theorem: The sum of the areas of the two squares on the legs (<i>a</i> and <i>b</i>) equals the area of the square on the hypotenuse (<i>c</i>).</div>
</div>
